tool.name: COG_Explore

param.name: in_nc_file
param.dialogReference: A raw satellite data NetCDF generated by the COG Fetch module. Input NetCDF must have coordinates for x, y and time.

param.name: out_folder
param.dialogReference: Output folder for the visualisation data (i.e., a cloud raster format file).

param.name: in_veg_idx
param.expression: MAVI | NDVI | EVI | SAVI | MSAVI | SLAVI | kNDVI | TCG
param.dialogReference:
The vegetation index in which to visualise the data. The following vegetation indices are available:

- NDVI (Normalized Difference Vegetation Index)

- EVI (Enhanced Vegetation Index)

- SAVI (Soil-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- MSAVI (Modified Soil-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- SLAVI (Specific Leaf Area Vegetation Index)

- MAVI (Moisture-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- kNDVI (Non-linear Normalized Vegetation Index)

- TCG (Tasselled Cap Greenness)

The default index is set to MAVI, which performs well in the Pilbara region of Western Australia.

param.name: in_fmask_flags
param.expression: NoData | Valid | Cloud | Shadow | Snow | Water
param.dialogReference:
Pixel classes provided by the DEA Fmask algorithm. The DEA Landsat and Sentinel satellite image products come with a mask band to assist in removing clouds, shadow, nodata, etc. Only selected pixel classes shown here will be used in analysis, whilst all others will be masked out (and later interpolated).

The default values include Valid, Snow and Water classes, and all others are masked out.

param.name: in_max_cloud
param.dialogReference:
The maximum percentage of cloud cover allowed within a satellite image before it is discarded from analysis. A value of 0 will return all satellite data with no registered cloud cover.

As a general rule of thumb, the smaller your study area the lower this value should be. The default value is 10%.

param.name: in_interpolate
param.dialogReference:
If checked, linear interpolation is applied along the time dimension at each pixel of the input satellite image NetCDF so as to fill in missing pixels masked out via the DEA Fmask band.

The default is recommended.

tool.summary: Generates a vegetation index representation of raw satellite data obtained prior via the COG Fetch tool. This is helpful for visualising your study area's vegetation over time and opens the data up for temporal graphing.
